    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) is acknowledged; the gap is mitigated by the consistency of results across two independent laboratories and the conservative nature of the single test condition relative to in vivo loading. Overall evidence weight is sufficient to support regulatory submission of the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw design under Medium model risk classification. Decision: Accepted with documented gap.",
